I like using it when I&#x27;m filling an array with an indeterminate number of elements.  I&#x27;ve used this pattern a few times:<p><pre><code>    foo foos[255];
    int ct = 0;

    if (<condition for adding first element>)
        foos[ct++] = foo1;

    if (<condition for adding second element>)
        foos[ct++] = foo2;

    ...

    for (int i = 0; i < ct; i++) {
        /* do something with foos[i] */
    }
</code></pre>
IMHO, this is more concise and readable than separating the increment and assignment into two lines.
